A vast, dark ocean surface stretching to the horizon at golden hour, with thick ribbons of iridescent black oil spreading across the water in swirling, organic patterns that catch the dying sunlight in sickly rainbows of purple, green, and amber. In the distance, a lone pelican struggles to take flight, its wings heavy and slicked. The sky above is a gradient of burnt orange fading to deep crimson, reflecting off both the clean water and the contaminated slicks, creating a disturbing contrast between natural beauty and industrial devastation. The composition is shot from a low angle just above the water's surface, emphasizing the endless expanse of pollution meeting pristine sea. Photorealistic style with hyper-detailed water textures and authentic oil viscosity, dramatic cinematic lighting.
